A worker was rushed to hospital after his hand was stuck in a printing press in Westmead, Pinetown in KwaZulu-Natal on Tuesday. Netcare 911 paramedics and their rescue unit were alerted to the industrial accident. Netcare 911 spokesperson, Chris Botha said reports revealed that a worker got his hand trapped in the rollers of a printing press, Highway Mail reported. Paramedics arrived and found the man to have suffered moderate injuries. The Netcare 911 rescue officer managed to free the man s hand from the rollers. He was stabilised and then taken to a Durban hospital, said Botha. Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.